title: San Benito makes big leap in RGVSports.com top 10 poll
text:
San Benito makes big leap in RGVSports.com top 10 poll RGVSPORTS.COM Brownsville Herald 
San Benito made the biggest jump in this week’s RGVSports.com top 10 high school football poll heading into Week 8. 
With its impressive 22-21 win last week at Harlingen High, the Greyhounds lept from ninth to fourth in the poll. The Cardinals dropped from third to sixth. 
San Benito and Harlingen High is each 4-2. Each plays fellow top 10 teams this week. San Benito plays host to Brownsville Veterans Memorial, and Harlingen High welcomes Los Fresnos. 
Los Fresnos is now third and undefeated at 6-0. Weslaco High is fifth with a 4-2 record and plays Edinburg North this week after a bye last week. 
Brownsville Veterans is seventh and 6-0 after taking care of Hanna on Saturday. Sharyland High is eighth and coming off a bye.
